      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals monitored; force and moment equilibrium residuals below 1e-4 at each load step.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear solver convergence was monitored across all 25 load increments. Force residuals remained below 5e-5 and moment residuals below 8e-5, well within the specified tolerance. No solver divergence events were recorded."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of model setup by a second analyst; documented checklist completed prior to each simulation run.",
      "rationale": "A peer review checklist covering boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and load application was completed by an independent analyst before production runs. No use errors were identified during review."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Continuum elastoplastic model with isotropic hardening used for titanium alloy; contact modeled with augmented Lagrangian; validated against published material data.",
      "rationale": "The model employs a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity formulation calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V coupon test data (yield 930 MPa, UTS 1000 MPa). Screw-rod and rod-block contact interactions use augmented Lagrangian with friction coefficient 0.2 as reported in the literature. Model form is appropriate for the quasi-static compression-bending regime."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties sourced from traceable coupon tests; geometry derived from CMM measurements of production hardware; sensitivity analysis performed on key inputs.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield stress, and tangent modulus were derived from tensile coupon tests of the same Ti-6Al-4V lot used in construct fabrication. Geometry was imported from CMM-measured CAD. One-at-a-time sensitivity analysis showed QoI variation below 4% across ±10% perturbations of all primary inputs."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs tested across two independent laboratories; sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASTM E2782.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled and tested: six at Laboratory A and five at Laboratory B. Inter-laboratory variability was assessed and found acceptable (CV < 5%). Sample size supports the E/uval metric computation with adequate statistical power."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU operating conditions; at minimum two distinct load levels or boundary condition configurations evaluated experimentally.",
      "rationale": "Experimental validation was conducted exclusively under the single standardized ASTM F1717 compression-bending configuration at a fixed 10-mm offset. While this configuration is clinically representative and the protocol is well-established, engineering judgment supports that the single-condition dataset is sufficient given the linear-dominated response regime and the robustness demonstrated across both laboratories."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Model boundary conditions and loading match experimental setup to within documented tolerances; fixture compliance accounted for.",
      "rationale": "Load application point, offset distance, and boundary constraint locations in the FEA model were matched to the physical test fixture dimensions measured by the laboratory. Machine compliance was characterized and excluded from displacement measurements. Input equivalency is confirmed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison using E/uval metric; all QoIs satisfy E/uval < 1.96 and percent difference < 10%.",
      "rationale": "All three primary QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both acceptance criteria: maximum E/uval = 1.61 and maximum percent difference = 7.1%. The model is confirmed to reproduce experimental behavior within pre-established bounds."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly link to the COU decision: construct stiffness and strength are the primary engineering performance metrics for regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the quantities specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly used in the 510(k) substantial equivalence comparison. These QoIs are fully relevant to the COU decision."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
